@startuml iOS Team Data Flow

title iOS Team Data Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE

' Actors
actor "iOS Developer" as dev
participant "Sub-agent\n(Alex)" as alex
participant "Sub-agent\n(Morgan - Tech Lead)" as morgan
participant "Skill\n(iOS Dev)" as skill
participant "Skill\n(Code Review)" as review
participant "Knowledge Base" as kb
participant "JIRA MCP" as jira
participant "Confluence MCP" as conf
participant "Git MCP" as git
participant "Simulator MCP" as sim

' External
participant "JIRA Server" as jira_server
participant "Confluence Server" as conf_server
participant "GitHub Server" as github_server
participant "iOS Simulator" as simulator_app

== Task Initiation ==

dev -> alex : "Complete iOS-1234"
activate alex

alex -> alex : Parse request
alex -> skill : Load iOS Development Skill
activate skill

skill -> alex : Workflow steps loaded

== Knowledge Enrichment ==

alex -> kb : Request team context
activate kb

kb -> conf : Fetch iOS coding standards
activate conf
conf -> conf_server : API call
conf_server --> conf : Standards doc
conf --> kb : iOS coding standards
deactivate conf

kb -> conf : Fetch iOS project context
activate conf
conf -> conf_server : API call
conf_server --> conf : Screen flows & specs
conf --> kb : iOS project context
deactivate conf

kb --> alex : Team context enriched
deactivate kb

note right of alex
  Agent now has:
  - Ticket context
  - iOS coding standards
  - Screen flows
  - UI specifications
end note

== Development Workflow ==

skill -> alex : Execute Step 1: Get Requirements

alex -> jira : Get ticket iOS-1234
activate jira
jira -> jira_server : REST API call
jira_server --> jira : Ticket details
jira --> alex : Ticket info
deactivate jira

skill -> alex : Execute Step 2: Design UI

alex -> alex : Design screen & flow
note right
  Uses iOS project context
  to follow existing patterns
end note

skill -> alex : Execute Step 3: Implement

alex -> git : Create branch
activate git
git -> github_server : git checkout -b
github_server --> git : Branch created
git --> alex : Branch ready
deactivate git

alex -> alex : Write iOS code
note right
  - SwiftUI/UIKit views
  - ViewModel logic
  - API integration
end note

skill -> alex : Execute Step 4: Test on Simulator

alex -> sim : Build & run on simulator
activate sim
sim -> simulator_app : Build app
simulator_app --> sim : App running
sim -> sim : Run UI tests
sim --> alex : Tests passed
deactivate sim

skill -> alex : Execute Step 5: Self-Review

alex -> review : Load Code Review Skill
activate review
review -> alex : Checklist loaded

alex -> alex : Run review checklist
note right
  - MVVM patterns
  - Memory management
  - UI guidelines
end note

review --> alex : Review passed
deactivate review

skill -> alex : Execute Step 6: Create PR

alex -> git : Commit & create PR
activate git
git -> github_server : git commit & push
github_server --> git : Committed
git -> github_server : Create PR
github_server --> git : PR #789 created
git --> alex : PR URL
deactivate git

alex -> jira : Update ticket status
activate jira
jira -> jira_server : Transition to In Review
jira_server --> jira : Updated
jira --> alex : Success
deactivate jira

== Tech Lead Review ==

morgan -> git : Review PR #789
activate git
git -> github_server : Get PR details
github_server --> git : PR diff
git --> morgan : PR content
deactivate git

morgan -> review : Load Code Review Skill
activate review
review -> morgan : Checklist loaded

morgan -> kb : Get iOS coding standards
activate kb
kb --> morgan : Standards loaded
deactivate kb

morgan -> sim : Test on simulator
activate sim
sim -> simulator_app : Build app
simulator_app --> sim : App running
sim --> morgan : UI verified
deactivate sim

morgan -> morgan : Review against standards
note right
  - Architecture patterns
  - Performance
  - Accessibility
end note

morgan -> git : Approve PR
activate git
git -> github_server : Add approval
github_server --> git : Approved
git --> morgan : Success
deactivate git

review --> morgan : Review complete
deactivate review

== Response to User ==

alex --> dev : Task completed!
deactivate skill
deactivate alex

note right of dev
  **Summary:**
  - Branch: feature/iOS-1234
  - PR: #789 (Approved)
  - JIRA: Ready to Merge
  - Simulator: Tests passed
end note

@enduml
